\begin_layout Subsection
Interest Rates Interpretation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Rate of return
\series default
 is the return required by an investor to accept an investment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Discount rate 
\series default
is the time value of money (FCF discount).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Opportunity cost
\series default
 is the rate foregone by choosing a particular investment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus, the nominal interest rate is the sum of: the real interest rate +
 inflation + risk premium + liquidity premium + maturity premium.
\end_layout

